                  a: 'Open transactions hold an xmin horizon. PostgreSQL\'s MVCC model keeps all row versions newer than the oldest active xmin, so autovacuum cannot reclaim any dead tuples created after that transaction started. Over hours, this causes unbounded table bloat, slower sequential scans, and wasted disk. Monitoring idle-in-transaction sessions in pg_stat_activity is a standard production health check.'
                }
