        intro: 'A query that runs fine on 10 000 rows in dev will devastate a 50 million row production table. EXPLAIN ANALYZE, pg_stat_statements, and autovacuum tuning are the three tools that prevent that gap from becoming an incident.',
        insight: 'EXPLAIN ANALYZE is not a diagnostic tool you reach for when something breaks — it is a verification step you run before shipping any query that touches more than a thousand rows.',
        points: [
