                  q: 'What does the cost number in EXPLAIN output represent?',
                  a: 'Cost is a unitless estimate from the planner\'s cost model: cost=startup..total. Startup cost is the estimated work before the first row can be returned (e.g., building a hash table). Total cost is the estimated work to return all rows. It is not wall-clock time — it is a relative number used by the planner to compare alternative execution plans. A higher cost just means the planner estimated more work, not that it will be slower in wall time.'
